The IETT, the '''Institute for Transtextual and Transcultural Studies''' ({{lang-fr|Institut d'études transtextuelles et transculturelles|link=no}} (IETT)), is a research institute based in [[Lyon]], [[France]], attached to the doctoral school of [[Jean Moulin University Lyon 3]]. It focuses on analysis of how the world was conceived from colonialist relations, notions of gender, and techno-economic ideologies.<ref>{{cite web|title=Institut d'Etudes Transtextuelles et Transculturelles|url=https://iett.world/|website=iett.world|publisher=IETT|accessdate=25 November 2017}}</ref> Its current director is [[Gregory B. Lee]].{{citation needed|date=November 2017}}

The IETT serves as a laboratory to the French Network for Asian Studies (GIS Asia)<ref>{{cite web|title=GIS Partners|url=http://www.gis-reseau-asie.org/gis-partners|website=gis-reseau-asie.org|publisher=GIS Asie - Réseau Asie & Pacifique|accessdate=25 November 2017}}</ref> and is a member of Europe in a Networked World (E-NeW).<ref>{{cite web|title=Europe in a Networked World|url=http://enew.world/|website=enew.world|accessdate=25 November 2017}}</ref> The IETT publishes the multilingual [[academic journal]] ''Transtext(e)s-Transcultures: A Journal of Global Cultural Studies''.<ref>{{cite web|title=Presentation|url=https://transtexts.revues.org/246|website=Transtext(e)s Transcultures|publisher=revues.org|accessdate=25 November 2017}}</ref>

